						               													<description>A dead body was found on a rainy night.&amp;#10;You have to reconstruct the crime to find out the murderer, and prevent further tragedies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Case #02 is co-operative real-time deduction card game. Players need to exchange alibi cards for more clues. And have to find out the culprit who has no alibi. Players will take points if they successfully determined the culprit before any victims are killed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This murder-themed game is a game of looking for two true criminals out of nine suspects in a limited time of three minutes. The hint for the perpetrator is limited to the number of the investigators, and not only the time but also the new victims (the people who thought they were suspects are killed by the criminals!) As the reasoning is delayed. It does not matter if you resolve the case beyond three minutes, but the only thing left is the wound.&amp;#10;And the opportunity to point out the killer is only once per game, regardless of the number of players and who is calling it! If this is a single chance, and you can not match the truth, then everyone will be defeated.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
